# Graficas 2D con @{plot}
> Funciones matematicas, anotaciones, heatmaps

## Funciones trigonometricas
@{plot}
x = -6.28 : 6.28
y = -1.5 : 1.5
y = sin(x) | color: #2196f3 | width: 2 | label: "sin(x)"
y = cos(x) | color: #f44336 | width: 2 | label: "cos(x)"
hline 0 #ccc
vline 0 #ccc
point 0 0 #333
text 0.3 1.1 "1" size:11 color:#888
text 0.3 -1.1 "-1" size:11 color:#888
@{end plot}

## Parametros
A = 3
omega = 2*pi/5
y_max = A * sin(pi/2)